{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6ef99c2a-f1c8-46fa-9dbc-ddaaeee24f04","content":"This template is **not quite ready** to publish. Here are the issues:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation: `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`\n\n**Missing recommended fields:**\n- `groupIdentity` — needed for NuGet discovery and versioning across related templates\n- `precedence` — helps the engine resolve conflicts when multiple versions are installed\n- `description` — NuGet listing will look empty without it\n- `preferNameDirectory` — standard for project templates\n\n**Other observations:**\n- `identity` and `author` use placeholder values (`MyCompany…`) — replace with your real org name before publishing\n- The `Framework` symbol works but isn't wired to a `replaces` or `TargetFrameworkOverride` — it won't actually change the `.csproj` TFM unless you add that plumbing\n- No `postActions` for restoring packages (`dotnet restore`) — a common convenience\n\n**Minimum fixes to be publish-ready:**\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\",\n  \"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi\",   // add\n  \"precedence\": 100,                      // add\n  \"description\": \"A Web API template…\",  // add\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nOnce you add a description, a proper groupIdentity, and wire up the Framework symbol, it's good to go.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"19fe7ccb-a6c2-4681-8f85-04ac2110d74e","outputTokens":338,"requestId":"601B:16BC0E:5056EDB:587E914:69F9FA06"},"id":"e4982be5-0487-49ce-b303-5802bc38254b","timestamp":"2026-05-05T14:09:21.683Z","parentId":"6376701b-a3fa-4297-adc6-b3156d4ce2d2"}
